Female/immature male.description: Female/immature male Hepatic Tanagers have a heavier bill than Western Tanagers. They also have paler unmarked wings whereas female/nonbreeding male Westerns have darker wings with 2 wingbars.

Immature male.description: Immature male Summer Tanagers can look similar to nonbreeding male Western Tanagers but, Summer Tanagers do not have wingbars while Western Tanagers do.

Female.description: Female Summer Tanagers are yellow overall with plain wings whereas female/nonbreeding Western Tanagers have darker wings marked by 2 wingbars.
Scarlet Tanagers do not normally overlap with the range of Western Tanagers. Females do not have wingbars like female Western Tanagers.

Breeding male.description: Although American Goldfinches are yellow and black they are much smaller and daintier than Western Tanagers, with smaller bills and more slender proportions.

Female.description: Bullock's Orioles have thinner and pointier bills than Western Tanagers.
